<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-12-27T18:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-12-27T18:36:00-05:00" n="431" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d431">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.51/693: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-12-27T17:00:00-06:36"><hi rend="italic">December 27,
                                        1921—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 9:19
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>215. Eduardo Iturbide left for New York last night as Obregon’s
                            representative to resume the financial discussions initiated with Lamont
                            last October. Iturbide informed me that he has very full powers.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>